news.title: The Economic Times Real Estate Awards 2022-West rewards excellence in industry
news.para: The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2022 - West was graced by the presence of chief guest Irfan A Kazi, Chief Investment Officer, SWAMIH Investment Fund.

news.title: Nagpur civic body all set to collect and reuse construction, demolition waste
news.para: The process to appoint private operator for the purpose has been completed in just two days as against the usual 30-45 days, as the state has authorised municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B to act as administrator of the NMC.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to discuss high-rises in periphery, ESZ with states
news.para: The decision was taken in a recent meeting chaired by UT adviser Dharam Pal, who also reviewed the status of implementation of Chandigarh Master Plan-2031.

news.title: Mysuru development body recovers six acres of land worth Rs 120 crore in Vijayanagar
news.para: About 20 sites of 30x40 dimension can be developed in every acre and every site could fetch approximately nearly Rs 1 crore. On average, Muda would get Rs 25 crore for every developed acre.

news.title: Nalgonda plot auction price reduced to Rs 7,000 per square yard
news.para: Collector Prashant Patil said a large number of bidders had shown interest in the auction of the plots which will take place from March 14-17.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to come out with land pooling policy draft
news.para: The UT administration has already planned to make Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) the nodal agency for the land pooling policy to utilise available vacant land in the city as per the Master Plan, 2031.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Rs 8.84 crore property tax rebate for Bopal-Ghuma residents
news.para: ​The civic body has announced a discount for the newly added areas such as the Bopal-Ghuma municipality, and the gram panchayats of Sanathal, Vishalpur, Aslali, Geratnagar, and Khodiyar. Under the scheme, 75% discount will be given on 2021-22 bills, 50% on 2022-23 bills, and 25% on 2023-24 bills.

news.title: Chandigarh: Eight freehold residential sites' auction fetches Rs 37.5 crore
news.para: Assistant estate officer (AEO) Harjeet Singh Sandhu said the UT administration conducted the e-auction of the eight residential sites on freehold basis in sectors 33, 34, 35, 37 and 40 and against the reserve price of Rs 18 crore for them, they earned Rs 37.5 crore, an increase of 108%.

news.title: Indore: Over 13,000 properties sold in February, highest in last six months
news.para: A total of 13,289 properties were sold in February clocking a revenue of Rs 161 crore, up by 16 per cent from the same period a year ago. In February last year, 11,749 properties were registered in the city.

news.title: Maharashtra government nod to 300 sq ft SRA homes in Pune
news.para: Currently, tenements offered as part of the scheme are of 269 sq ft each. The urban development department on Tuesday issued a notification, allowing a 31 sq ft-increase in the size of the tenement.

news.title: Realtors urge Andhra Pradesh government to put off revision of land values
news.para: Speaking to reporters the other day, CREDAI general secretary KSC Bose said the realty sector in state has been struggling with various issues and upward revision of land values would further impact the industry.

news.title: A month on, two panels, two FIRs but no answers for Chintels Paradiso residents
news.para: All families in Tower D have lost their homes and are living in temporary accommodations, waiting in anger and agony for an answer about the fate of their homes.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to approve real estate projects in 30 days
news.para: KMC will now coordinate with state agencies and sanction plans within 30 working days from its application. “After the state agencies give their clearance, KMC will give its sanction within a fortnight to a month,” Hakim said.

news.title: MahaRERA projects may get property cards soon
news.para: The scheme to issue property cards to flat owners may soon start with MahaRERA-registered projects, a senior revenue official said on Wednesday.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance finalises rights issue, seeks up to 2,500 crore
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's loan disbursements during the third quarter to December 31, 2021 was 12% lower at Rs 2,828 crore compared to Rs 3,203 crore in the year ago period.
